      "writtenOn": "2019-09-11T23:20:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry I should\u0027ve given more context. I wasn\u0027t sure if you were able to access the bug (https://bugs.fuchsia.dev/p/fuchsia/issues/detail?id\u003d36439).\n\nI work under Fuchsia in the toolchain team and noticed that Clang got a new warning, -Wsizeof-array-div (https://reviews.llvm.org/D67287), which trickled down to our builders and caused our bots to go red since we have `-Wall -Werror`. The warning just points out instances when we have a `sizeof(array) / sizeof(type)` expression, but `type` is not the same size as the element type in `array`.\n\nNormally when a new warning comes in, I try to either clean instances where it appears internally in Fuchsia, but in the case of third party libraries, silence it temporarily since I\u0027m not familiar with other code bases. I mainly did a clean build using the revision that this patch came in and found that this comes up when building skia.\n\nWhen building I stopped at the first instance this warning appeared, so I wasn\u0027t sure if this warning would appear more times, but it could also be the case that it just appears once. I can move this to gn/BUILD.gn if it appears in multiple areas, otherwise I also don\u0027t mind addressing the areas where this warning is diagnosed. In either case, I mainly just want to keep our bots green to make our next rolls smooth and not have any other errors hiding behind new Clang warnings.",
